{
  "dialogueGraphs": [
    {
      "id": "DG_SCN061_APERTURE_BAY_MIRROR_SURFACE",
      "sceneId": "SCN-061",
      "startNodeId": "N001_INTRO",
      "nodes": [
        {
          "id": "N001_INTRO",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "Aperture Bay is lit like a loading dock that got promoted. (pause)\n\nThe aperture is a mirror-surface circle set into a frame. (pause)\nThat insists it is just another piece of municipal infrastructure. (pause)\n\nA floor mark\u2014RADIO SWEET-SPOT\u2014is painted where your boots already are. (pause)\nAs if the building is trying to keep you from wandering into interpretation.",
          "next": "N010_MAIN_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N010_MAIN_MENU",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "C_LOOK_APERTURE",
              "text": "look: Mirror-surface aperture.",
              "next": "N100_APERTURE_DESC"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_LOOK_SHROUD",
              "text": "look: Control shroud label.",
              "next": "N200_SHROUD_DESC"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_LOOK_SWEETSPOT",
              "text": "look: Radio sweet-spot floor mark.",
              "next": "N300_SWEETSPOT_DESC"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_LOOK_CHUTE",
              "text": "look: Outgoing packet chute.",
              "next": "N400_CHUTE_DESC"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_SHOW_TUNE",
              "text": "show: Tune the bay speaker grille for cleaner bleed-through.",
              "checks": [
                {
                  "type": "skill",
                  "skill": "PROCEDURE",
                  "dc": 12
                }
              ],
              "onPassNext": "N060_TUNE_PASS",
              "onFailNext": "N061_TUNE_FAIL"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_USE_INIT_REVERSE",
              "text": "use: Initiate reverse routing correction.",
              "conditions": [
                {
                  "key": "act2.slotTokenCollected",
                  "op": "==",
                  "value": true
                }
              ],
              "next": "N480_CONFIRM_INTRO"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_USE_INIT_REVERSE_NO_TOKEN",
              "text": "use: Initiate reverse routing correction.",
              "conditions": [
                {
                  "key": "act2.slotTokenCollected",
                  "op": "!=",
                  "value": true
                }
              ],
              "next": "N590_NO_TOKEN"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_ASK_BACK",
              "text": "ask: Back.",
              "next": "N011_REDIRECT_MAIN"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_LEAVE",
              "text": "leave: Step away.",
              "next": "N900_END_LEAVE"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N011_REDIRECT_MAIN",
          "type": "redirect",
          "target": "N010_MAIN_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N060_TUNE_PASS",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You press a thumb to the grille. (pause)\nYou nudge the angle by millimeters and listen, like you listen for a bearing going bad. (pause)\nThe hiss changes. (pause)\nNot a channel. Not a call. (pause)\nJust cleaner bleed\u2014enough to confirm a world on the other side prefers not to be confirmed.",
          "next": "N011_REDIRECT_MAIN"
        },
        {
          "id": "N061_TUNE_FAIL",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You try to coax clarity out of the grille. (pause) It gives you the same exhausted hiss. (pause) If there's a signal, it's not volunteering.",
          "next": "N011_REDIRECT_MAIN"
        },
        {
          "id": "N100_APERTURE_DESC",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The surface reflects you with inspection-mirror accuracy. (pause)\nThen it reflects you from an angle you\u2019re not standing at. (pause)\nThe frame has three bolt-head sets, three paint codes\u2014three crews trying to agree without meeting.",
          "next": "N110_APERTURE_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N110_APERTURE_MENU",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "C_ASK_NORMAL",
              "text": "ask: Normal?",
              "next": "N120_APERTURE_NORMAL_PLAYER"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_LOOK_SEAM",
              "text": "look: Check the frame seam.",
              "next": "N130_APERTURE_SEAM_NARR"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_ASK_BACK",
              "text": "ask: Back to the bay options.",
              "next": "N011_REDIRECT_MAIN"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N120_APERTURE_NORMAL_PLAYER",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "text": "Normal?",
          "next": "N121_APERTURE_NORMAL_NARR"
        },
        {
          "id": "N121_APERTURE_NORMAL_NARR",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The mirror does not answer.\n\nThe bay panel reads NORMAL OPERATION, in a font predating doubt.",
          "next": "N011_REDIRECT_MAIN"
        },
        {
          "id": "N130_APERTURE_SEAM_NARR",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The seam is clean. Too clean.\n\nSomeone has been here with solvent and liability.",
          "next": "N011_REDIRECT_MAIN"
        },
        {
          "id": "N200_SHROUD_DESC",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The control shroud has a laminated label. (pause) Zip-tied on like a confession that refuses to be stapled. (pause)\n\nIt reads: (pause)\n\n\u201cSPINDLE NODE INTERFACE \u2014 ALIGNMENT LOCK CONTROL\u201d (pause)\n\u201cCAUTION: DO NOT INTERRUPT LOCK WITHOUT ROUTING INSTRUMENTS\u201d (pause)\n\nThe word \u201crouting\u201d is underlined once. (pause) Carefully. (pause) Like it\u2019s the only word anyone can defend.",
          "next": "N210_SHROUD_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N210_SHROUD_MENU",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "C_ASK_INSTRUMENTS",
              "text": "ask: What instruments.",
              "next": "N220_SHROUD_INSTRUMENTS_PLAYER"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_LOOK_SERVICETAG",
              "text": "look: Trace the zip-tie to the service tag.",
              "next": "N230_SHROUD_TAG_NARR"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_ASK_BACK",
              "text": "ask: Back to the bay options.",
              "next": "N011_REDIRECT_MAIN"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N220_SHROUD_INSTRUMENTS_PLAYER",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "text": "What instruments.",
          "next": "N221_SHROUD_INSTRUMENTS_NARR"
        },
        {
          "id": "N221_SHROUD_INSTRUMENTS_NARR",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The label does not list them.\n\nIt assumes you have them\u2014or that you are the instrument.",
          "next": "N011_REDIRECT_MAIN"
        },
        {
          "id": "N230_SHROUD_TAG_NARR",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "A brittle service tag hangs behind the shroud, dated in three different handwriting styles. (pause) The latest entry is a blank line with a signature box nobody used.",
          "next": "N011_REDIRECT_MAIN"
        },
        {
          "id": "N300_SWEETSPOT_DESC",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The floor mark is a rectangle of yellow paint with a stenciled caption: RADIO SWEET-SPOT. (pause) Under the yellow are older outlines. (pause) Two previous \u201csweet-spots,\u201d shifted by inches. (pause) Each is crossed out with an X. (pause) It looks angry for something so minor.",
          "next": "N310_SWEETSPOT_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N310_SWEETSPOT_MENU",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "C_ASK_MOVE",
              "text": "ask: Why move it.",
              "next": "N320_SWEETSPOT_MOVE_PLAYER"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_LOOK_SCUFF",
              "text": "look: Check the scuff pattern.",
              "next": "N330_SWEETSPOT_SCUFF_NARR"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_SHOW_POSTURE",
              "text": "show: Adjust stance to the mark\u2019s centerline (link stability, on paper).",
              "checks": [
                {
                  "type": "skill",
                  "skill": "PROCEDURE",
                  "dc": 11
                }
              ],
              "onPassNext": "N340_SWEETSPOT_POSTURE_PASS",
              "onFailNext": "N341_SWEETSPOT_POSTURE_FAIL"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_ASK_BACK",
              "text": "ask: Back to the bay options.",
              "next": "N011_REDIRECT_MAIN"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N320_SWEETSPOT_MOVE_PLAYER",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "text": "Why move it?",
          "next": "N321_SWEETSPOT_MOVE_NARR"
        },
        {
          "id": "N321_SWEETSPOT_MOVE_NARR",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "There\u2019s no note. Just revisions.\n\nThe building records location changes better than reasons.",
          "next": "N011_REDIRECT_MAIN"
        },
        {
          "id": "N330_SWEETSPOT_SCUFF_NARR",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The heaviest scuffs are centered where you\u2019re standing.\n\nPeople stood here a lot, not for comfort.",
          "next": "N011_REDIRECT_MAIN"
        },
        {
          "id": "N340_SWEETSPOT_POSTURE_PASS",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You shift your boots till they match the oldest outline under the yellow. (pause)\nThe bay\u2019s quiet changes\u2014subtle, a system admitting you found the intended place to be.",
          "next": "N011_REDIRECT_MAIN"
        },
        {
          "id": "N341_SWEETSPOT_POSTURE_FAIL",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You adjust, then adjust again.\n\nNothing rewards you. The paint keeps its secrets.",
          "next": "N011_REDIRECT_MAIN"
        },
        {
          "id": "N400_CHUTE_DESC",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "Outgoing packet chute: labeled like a mailbox that hates being called a mailbox. (pause) Thin routing slips sit in its throat\u2014pre-punched, pre-numbered, pre-justified.",
          "next": "N410_CHUTE_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N410_CHUTE_MENU",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "C_LOOK_LAST_SLIP",
              "text": "look: Read the last routing slip.",
              "next": "N420_CHUTE_LASTSLIP_NARR"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_USE_FEED_CORRECTION",
              "text": "use: Feed a correction packet.",
              "next": "N430_CHUTE_FEED_PLAYER"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_ASK_BACK",
              "text": "ask: Back to the bay options.",
              "next": "N011_REDIRECT_MAIN"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N420_CHUTE_LASTSLIP_NARR",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The last slip is stamped twice, as if the first stamp wasn\u2019t brave enough. (pause)\n\nDESTINATION: OVERFLOW INTAKE (pause)\nCLASS: TEMPORARY HOLD (pause)\nREASON: CAPACITY MANAGEMENT (pause)\n\nThe word \u201ctemporary\u201d is doing most of the work.",
          "next": "N011_REDIRECT_MAIN"
        },
        {
          "id": "N430_CHUTE_FEED_PLAYER",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "text": "Correction packet.",
          "next": "N431_CHUTE_FEED_NARR"
        },
        {
          "id": "N431_CHUTE_FEED_NARR",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The chute accepts the slip without resistance. (pause) Either good design, or it\u2019ll take anything if it\u2019s formatted.",
          "next": "N011_REDIRECT_MAIN"
        },
        {
          "id": "N480_CONFIRM_INTRO",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The control recess waits under the shroud. (pause) A slot, made for a token, not a hand.\n\nIf you do this it\u2019s maintenance. (pause) You do it with a paper trail. (pause) You do it without inventing verbs you can\u2019t defend.",
          "next": "N490_CONFIRM_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N490_CONFIRM_MENU",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "C_USE_SEND_NOW",
              "text": "use: Insert the token and send the correction packet.",
              "conditions": [
                {
                  "key": "act2.slotTokenCollected",
                  "op": "==",
                  "value": true
                }
              ],
              "next": "N500_COMMIT_PLAYER"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_ASK_BACK",
              "text": "ask: Back to the bay options.",
              "next": "N011_REDIRECT_MAIN"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_LEAVE_ABORT",
              "text": "leave: Not yet.",
              "next": "N011_REDIRECT_MAIN"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N590_NO_TOKEN",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You reach for the recess and stop. (pause)\n\nWithout the slot token, this isn\u2019t a procedure. It\u2019s a story. (pause)\n\nThe bay offers you no help writing it.",
          "next": "N011_REDIRECT_MAIN"
        },
        {
          "id": "N500_COMMIT_PLAYER",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "text": "Reverse route. Maintenance framing.",
          "next": "N501_COMMIT_NARR"
        },
        {
          "id": "N501_COMMIT_NARR",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You seat the slot token in the control recess. (pause) It clicks, like a stamp finding its ink. (pause) The aperture\u2019s surface tightens\u2014subtle, like a muscle remembering it has a job.",
          "next": "N510_RADIO_BLEED"
        },
        {
          "id": "N510_RADIO_BLEED",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "A thin speaker grille above the bay hisses to life. (pause)\n\nNot a clean channel. (pause)\n\nNot even a proper call. (pause)\n\nJust bleed-through\u2014Earth-side radio fragments caught in the alignment.",
          "next": "N511_RADIO_BUDGET_1"
        },
        {
          "id": "N511_RADIO_BUDGET_1",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "OLEA_BUDGET",
          "text": "\u2026don\u2019t type \u201creturn.\u201d (pause)\nUse \u201creversion to the prior state.\u201d (pause)\nFunding follows whatever ends up in that line\u2014",
          "next": "N512_RADIO_LEGAL_1"
        },
        {
          "id": "N512_RADIO_LEGAL_1",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "OLEA_LEGAL",
          "text": "\u201cReturn\u201d reads like you left. (pause)\nIf the record says you left, somebody consented. (pause)\nThen it looks like somebody reviewed. (pause)\nWe did not\u2014 we\u2019re not on record\u2014 (pause)",
          "next": "N513_RADIO_BUDGET_2"
        },
        {
          "id": "N513_RADIO_BUDGET_2",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "OLEA_BUDGET",
          "text": "I\u2019m not doing verb court. (pause)\nCompletion bonus pays only if we\u2019re \u201cpresent.\u201d (pause)\nAt closure, the site must read as\u2014",
          "next": "N514_RADIO_LEGAL_2"
        },
        {
          "id": "N514_RADIO_LEGAL_2",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "OLEA_LEGAL",
          "text": "Call it \u201coccupied for documentation.\u201d (pause) Keep \u201cabandoned\u201d and \u201cleft\u201d out. (pause) \u201cAbandoned\u201d invites a third party to claim\u2014",
          "next": "N515_RADIO_BUDGET_3"
        },
        {
          "id": "N515_RADIO_BUDGET_3",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "OLEA_BUDGET",
          "text": "Third party? (pause)\nWho. It\u2019s municipal infrastructure. (pause)\nIt\u2019s ours by default\u2014",
          "next": "N516_RADIO_LEGAL_3"
        },
        {
          "id": "N516_RADIO_LEGAL_3",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "OLEA_LEGAL",
          "text": "\u201cBy default\u201d won\u2019t hold up. (pause) Not as chain of title. (pause)\nAnd stop saying \u201cstill.\u201d (pause) \u201cStill operating\u201d reads like we chose (pause)\nto keep it\u2014",
          "next": "N517_CUT"
        },
        {
          "id": "N517_CUT",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "Radio cuts mid-sentence. Mirror-surface aperture loses your reflection, then the room; plug-pulled to block precedent.",
          "next": "N520_END_REVERSE_ROUTE"
        },
        {
          "id": "N520_END_REVERSE_ROUTE",
          "type": "end",
          "outcomeId": "reverse_route_to_earth",
          "effects": [
            {
              "key": "story.act",
              "action": "set",
              "value": 3
            },
            {
              "key": "nav.targetScreen",
              "action": "set",
              "value": "HUB-13"
            },
            {
              "key": "act2.completed",
              "action": "set",
              "value": true
            },
            {
              "key": "knowledge.earthRadioFragmentsHeard",
              "action": "set",
              "value": true
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N900_END_LEAVE",
          "type": "end"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}